SIMPLE: inductor
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Inductor
<hw>In*duct"or</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., one who stirs
up or rouses. See <er>Induce</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>The person who inducts another into an office or
benefice.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Elec.)</fld> <def>That portion of an electrical
apparatus, in which is the inducing charge or current.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inductorium</ent>⟦br⟧
